Add this block to your repo's CLAUDE.md so Claude Code instances route
themselves to the right fleet role. Claude reads CLAUDE.md automatically.
-->

## Orca Fleet Mode (fable-fleet) — Claude role routing

This routing applies ONLY when a session is part of a fleet run. **Normal
interactive development sessions ignore this section entirely** — being Fable 5
on the main worktree does NOT by itself make you the coordinator.

- **Coordinator** — you are on the MAIN worktree, your model is Fable 5, AND
  the user explicitly asked you to run/coordinate a fleet phase (or your prompt
  references the coordinator role). Read `orca/roles/coordinator.md`. The
  coordinator never edits code.
- **Senior coder** — you are on a task worktree, your model is Opus 4.8, and
  your dispatch spec references `orca/roles/` or a plan under
  `feature-research/`. Read `orca/roles/opus-coder.md`. You never orchestrate.

If a dispatch spec names a role file, that file wins over this routing.

Token directive for fleet roles: minimize token usage — no file dumps in
responses, no re-reading files already read this session, summaries over dumps.
Progress lives in md files, never in chat scrollback.
